cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation using convolutional neural networks. The use of generative adversarial networks also suggests a possible fit with the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The inclusion of an additional loss function and the use of dilated convolutions may also suggest a possible fit with the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the application of the method to medical image analysis may suggest a possible fit with the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
